content: What are some of the online engagement wins or observations you had this past week?

I shared out a link of new merch on the Kamala Harris store to a (very Harris/Walz friendly) subreddit and it got a good response.

People were commenting about the stuff they bought, a pretty good result from just a single post. Just reminding people about new releases feels like a very achievable way to generate support for the campaign
I created and shared a FB reel that received over 100 views; see attachments.
Nice! Facebook reels are set up to get much more engagement than just posting images, at least from what I’ve learned.
<@260982275506700288> You are correct…my latest posts are videos.  The images shared earlier were included in a slide show.
